For two weeks you will live like a wolf, but before the end of the term you must find the same tree and turn around it in the opposite direction. This way he will recover his human form.

0x029da9a70ed689a0.name: Kappa
0x029da9a70ed689a0.description: Lethal Demon that lives in rivers and ponds. Human form, small stature, reptilian appearance. It has a container on its head that, if it empties of water, the Kappa dies. He likes to eat children and cucumbers.

0x0530fe29b78a0a07.name: Rompo
0x0530fe29b78a0a07.description: Beast with the head of a hare, human ears, a skeleton-like body, the front arms of a badger, and the rear legs of a bear. It feeds only on human corpses and it is said to croon softly as it eats.

0x06760a2a75d88098.name: Tecelán
0x06760a2a75d88098.description: Entombed beneath a megalithic mound rests the Weaver of Carballás, a spectral sage who prophesies the end of the world.

0x06c70773d2a6a024.name: Tupilaq
0x06c70773d2a6a024.description: Avenging monster manufactured by a shaman through the use of animal parts (bones, skin, hair, tendons, etc.) and corpses of children. After the creature is given life by a ritual; and then placed in the sea to search and destroy a specific enemy.

0x07486ddf2209efaa.name: Sasabonsam
0x07486ddf2209efaa.description: This vampire lives in trees of the forests and feed on those who dare to wander into his domain. Instead of feet it has hooks, with which it hangs from the branches, and its teeth are made of iron.

0x081aa2cb06ba3719.name: Popobawa
0x081aa2cb06ba3719.description: Vampire with small pointed ears and one eye, assaults men at night, immobilizes and sodomizes them. It only attacks those who do not believe in it, although if the victim hides the attack, it will also assault the neighbors.

0x08762abe6824700e.name: Dhampir
0x08762abe6824700e.description: Result of the union of a vampire with a human, the Dhampir is a man with a large head, soft body and gelatinous bones. It is able to find vampires, which it hunts in exchange for a reward. It is normally born among the gypsies, but it can belong to any Balkan people.

0x122edf3c3492feb1.name: Shen-long
0x122edf3c3492feb1.description: Aquatic dragon that can change shape and cause mirages.

0x126f0bf4640702c1.name: Ninki Nanka
0x126f0bf4640702c1.description: Monster that hides in the swamps, with the body of a crocodile, the head of a horse with three horns and the neck of a giraffe. Very dangerous, especially for children who dare to enter alone in their domains.

0x144a3c2fbaffa821.name: Jepá
0x144a3c2fbaffa821.description: Huge boa that lives in rivers and lakes, able to create eddies to swallow men and canoes.

0x14885581c49a4257.name: Sengani
0x14885581c49a4257.description: Colossal, unpredictible, human-like beings with enormous strength and control over animals. They are associated with the god Haine.

0x189312e772d011d6.name: Şahmaran
0x189312e772d011d6.description: Queen of the wise snakes that live in the subsoil, Şahmaran is half snake and half woman.

0x1af12b22597a2148.name: Kăk-whăn’-û-ghăt Kǐg-û-lu’-nǐk
0x1af12b22597a2148.description: An elusive but dangerous animal, it usually has the shape of a killer whale, but can become a wolf to hunt on land.

0x24201e79abb94df0.name: Kukulkan
0x24201e79abb94df0.description: Kukulkan, a feathered serpentine deity, commands natural forces and symbolizes the link between humanity and divinity, heralding cosmic renewal and transformation.

0x26cc7173ce66cd16.name: Pua Tu Tahi
0x26cc7173ce66cd16.description: Giant monster clam of the deep that swallows boaters, the Pua Tu Tahi is one of the evil gods of fish in the Rata legend. It could emerge to the surface and look like a large island, while absorbing the boats that sailed nearby.

0x320f244c3b19f3d2.name: Wati-kutjaran
0x320f244c3b19f3d2.description: They are two lizard-men, who become wind when they are in danger. Benevolent, they travel the world destroying evil spirits.

0x32ad61aedd8f6b22.name: Maruxaina
0x32ad61aedd8f6b22.description: A mermaid that lives in an underwater cave and attracts sailors with her song. Some believe she does this to cause shipwreck, others that it is to provent accidents.

0x342a9c4d5712ec2a.name: Tsenahale
0x342a9c4d5712ec2a.description: The Tsenahale are two of the Anaye, or “Alien Gods”, who plagued the land of the Navajo after men and women were separated, being created from de union of a woman and a pile of feathers.

0x35a5d1af96049599.name: Zhar-Ptitsa
0x35a5d1af96049599.description: Fire bird that has magical properties. Large and majestic plumage that glows with a red light, like a bonfire. The feathers continue to glow brightly after being torn off. The song of this bird  heals the sick and gives sight to the blind. Each year, in the fall, Zhar-Ptitsa dies and is reborn in the spring.

0x3c9dd4b50c3ef468.name: Kizy
0x3c9dd4b50c3ef468.description: Spirit of evil, which harms people and eats their souls. He lives confined in the sea of the dead by order of the Old Mother, in the north, where heaven and earth meet.

0x41b7d7bd68875337.name: Tulpar
0x41b7d7bd68875337.description: Legendary animal, half horse and half raptor. It is linked to a human, his master, whom he will serve eternally, both in hunting and in war, with unwavering loyalty.

0x4aba8e818a71636a.name: Bunyip
0x4aba8e818a71636a.description: Aquatic creatures with a fearsome reputation for trapping and devouring humans, ever changing in appearance but always powerful.

0x4cb9598461a9aa21.name: Inkanyamba
0x4cb9598461a9aa21.description: Huge snake with a horse's head, lives in the waterfalls of Pietermaritzburg. Very active in summer, his anger causes seasonal storms.

0x54765a4c3a8e9b5a.name: Macihuatli
0x54765a4c3a8e9b5a.description: Evil spirits of women who, at the moment of their death, choose to continue seeking revenge. They appear at night in horse  and with a lot of makeup on their faces, looking for lovers. After seducing him, she becomes a monster with the rotten horse's head.

0x5f44ab400c5c0e17.name: Trempulcahue
0x5f44ab400c5c0e17.description: There are four old women who turn into whales every night to carry the souls of the dead. No alive can see them, and the souls have to pay their toll in precious stones.

0x617cb67bb49fc07a.name: Kanmare
0x617cb67bb49fc07a.description: Giant snake that protects the people and punishes those who break their law. Giver of life in the deserts, she is mistress of water.

0x6891f3133661fe69.name: Ifrit
0x6891f3133661fe69.description: Very powerful genius, created directly from the breath of Allah. Generally invisible, it can take many forms to deceive people or seize their will.

0x68969ec287a52dbe.name: Karkadann
0x68969ec287a52dbe.description: Lord of the desert, ferocious animal with body of buffalo and horn with medicinal properties.

0x6d855b49fb9dcfe8.name: Yeti
0x6d855b49fb9dcfe8.description: Ape-like being, taller than an average human, that inhabit the Himalayan region of Nepal, Bhutan, and Tibet. He carries a large stone as a weapon and makes a whistling swoosh sound.

0x6f6408aedfceefff.name: Iku-Turso
0x6f6408aedfceefff.description: Monster that inhabits both the Baltic Sea and the lakes, is extremely ferocious and evil. it has long tentacles and suckers, and there is no naval battle in which it does not participate.

0x76067738a7dd4730.name: Sasquatch
0x76067738a7dd4730.description: A large, hairy, muscular, bipedal ape-like creature, covered in dark brown hair.

0x78fc6986bf235dcd.name: Caaporá
0x78fc6986bf235dcd.description: Creature of the jungle, owner and protector of animals. She captivates the hunters and if she considers them good, she helps them in the hunt. If not, she will beat his dogs and, taking advantage of her invisibility, allows the prey to flee.

0x7a7bfdff2ea9609a.name: /Kaggen
0x7a7bfdff2ea9609a.description: Created by a shaman from human remains, this furry and malignant creature is able to change shape and even disappear (if he eats a stone). Kill cattle, steal, kidnap children and rape women.

0x7c6f7759783efdb1.name: Japiñuños
0x7c6f7759783efdb1.description: Very old demons, which take the form of beautiful flying women, with breasts as long as their hair, and a long tail. They trap people and steal their souls to make them one of them.

0x7db32a2e645e27d6.name: Nykur
0x7db32a2e645e27d6.description: Malignant creature similar to an amphibious horse, but with the body sticky and the hooves backwards. It lives in the depths of the sea and lakes, and come to the surface to try and lure passing humans to mount it. People who fall into the trap of riding it stay stuck to it, while the Nykur dives back into the water drowning the unwary.

0x7e8bba2ff0eb92f9.name: Dybbuk
0x7e8bba2ff0eb92f9.description: Souls trapped in this world by crime or an unfulfilled destiny, occupying the body of a living person, are exorcised by a rabbi.

0x832c2aeecbc4189e.name: Rahu
0x832c2aeecbc4189e.description: Mythical creature that has not body, only a head, and can swallow the sun or the moon causing eclipses.

0x8df75eae68b3af20.name: Muló
0x8df75eae68b3af20.description: After an unnatural death, a person can become an undead with a thirst for revenge. They wreak havoc, beating people, draining their blood and raping their old wives. Only a dhampir can hunt them down.

0x90f20e01a70a99cf.name: Droemerdene
0x90f20e01a70a99cf.description: He was the Canopus star and helped the first men to change from their kangaroo-like form, and protect them from his brother Moinee and many devils.

0x97836f0e95f302d9.name: Nei Tituaabine
0x97836f0e95f302d9.description: Is a red-naired maiden. After her death, three trees grew from her grave: a coconut from her head, a pandanus from her heels and an almond from her navel. She became a tree goddess.

0x980d2734537a2156.name: Mokèlé-mbèmbé
0x980d2734537a2156.description: A giant monster with a long neck, similar to a sauropod, lives on Lake Tele. He avoids encounters with human beings, but if he can not help it, he fights fiercely.

0xa1bbbfa0de5f9694.name: Haechi
0xa1bbbfa0de5f9694.description: Legendary animal with dog body, lion head and wings. He is able to eat fire. Protects from fires and disasters and represents justice and integrity.

0xaae0ad735264bb14.name: Kel Essuf
0xaae0ad735264bb14.description: Perverse spirits that inhabit the dunes of the desert. They are capable of disorienting travelers and causing their death by thirst and hunger.

0xb3877755683a76fa.name: Dudugera
0xb3877755683a76fa.description: Son of a woman and a god, Dudugera became scorching Sun to destroy the world. Only clouds can protect the world from its wrath.

0xb7049151375948e4.name: Tarasca
0xb7049151375948e4.description: Species of dragon of six short legs similar to those of a bear, a torso similar to the one of an ox with a shell of turtle to its back and a scaly tail that finish in the sting of a scorpion. Its head is similar to that of a lion with horse ears.

0xb7cf21d1e81a08d2.name: Nessie
0xb7cf21d1e81a08d2.description: Huge creature that inhabits Loch Ness, shaped like a plesiosaur. With an extremely elusive character, he shuns all contact with the human being. Its origin and customs are unknown, although it could be a dinosaur that survived the extinction of its congeners frozen in the lake.

0xba61dc216683ef61.description: By the spell of a shaman or by his own desire, a Sami can become a wolf, although only for periods of two weeks.
